⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Crime
node AHX · AHX · ⟦The Crime:AHX:88e63e⟧

WHO   — The Crime — the hate crime at the film's core
WHAT  — The unflinching centre: a hate crime depicted with deliberate horror, the act the whole film reckons backward and forward from.
WHERE — AHX · American History X (1998)  Framework inputs: American History X (1998, dir. Tony Kaye, New Line); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film refuses to let the hatred be abstract — it shows, gravely, what it does to real bodies.
HOW   — By staging the murder as horror, not spectacle, and treating the two men as victims of a hate crime.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the act the rest of the film orbits. Two men were murdered here for the colour of their skin. Do not look away from that.

